data.content:
Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()
{
    var service = new UserService();

    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(
        () => service.CreateUser(null, "John"));
}
```

**Why:** `[ExpectedException]` can't verify *which line* threw, so a different `ArgumentNullException` earlier in the test would silently pass. `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call. It also lets you inspect the exception:

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(
    () => service.CreateUser(null, "John"));

Assert.AreEqual("email", ex.ParamName);
```
